HEADWORD: Seminar
<hw>Sem`i*nar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. See
<er>Seminary</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A group of students
engaged, under the guidance of an instructor, in original research in a
particular line of study, and in the exposition of the results by
theses, lectures, etc.; -- formerly called also
<altname>seminary</altname>, now seldom used in this sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seminarist</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Seminarian</ent>⟦br⟧
